notes.note:
Email to client for missing information:

Good afternoon Jobanpreet, 
I have reviewed all of the documentation that has been submitted, and it appears as though we still need some information: 
- The Automobile Insurance Policy that was provided is not valid on the date of loss. The effective dates are from 07-22-2020 to 10-22-2020. Your date of loss is 05-08-2020, and therefore we need to see the insurance policy that was in effect on that date. As well, the insurance policy only lists "Auto #1" but does not list the vehicle information. We need to confirm that vehicle matches with the vehicle we have on file. 
- The Insurance police states that the average annual kilometers on the vehicle is roughly 12,000 kilometers per year. It appears as though the vehicle has been driven 73,505 kilometers in less than one year. Can you please provide more information as to the difference in kms?
Your assistance is greatly appreciated. 
Thanks, 
Sarah Gabor
